\section{Introduction}
The system is a program designed to manage utility consumption in this case water consumption for either domestic or commercial meters. The system is called "HAVEN PREPAID WATER SYSTEM". It enter the amount of money paid by a customer or user and calculates the number of units for the amount paid. The program features structured security via system token authentications, records management (that is; Create, Read, Update, Delete) for up to 50 distinct household records.

\section{System Constants and conditions}
The program required authentication and some fixed values for calculations for example;maintenance fee, charge for domestic meter and commercial meter and the alert safety limit. these values are listed below.
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{System Access PIN:} 4545
    \item \textbf{Fixed Maintenance Fee Deducted:} 500.0 UGX
    \item \textbf{Domestic Unit Rate:} 150.0 UGX per Unit
    \item \textbf{Commercial Unit Rate:} 250.0 UGX per Unit
    \item \textbf{Leakage Alert Safety Limit:} 50.0 Units per day
\end{itemize}

\section{Declaration of functions}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \texttt{int authenticate();} -- Validates user access by requesting for the system security PIN.
    \item \texttt{void addHousehold();} -- Allocates storage and activates a new customer record profile.
    \item \texttt{void searchHousehold();} -- Looks through the existing system registry to locate a targeted household profile.
