\section{Mathematical Business Logic}
The program works in a way that when a user or household owner makes a deposit(money),M, it deducts a maintenance fee,Fm of 500UGX and the balance(grossAmount),Mnet is used to calculate the units bought by dividing by the dynamicRate(for either domestic or commercial meter). The mathematical evaluation is modeled below:

\subsection{Calculation of gross amount}
Given a gross money $M$, the processing grossAmount $M_{net}$ is computed after a fixed maintenance fee ($F_m$) extraction:
\begin{equation}
M_{net} = M - F_m
\end{equation}
If $M \le F_m$, the operational routine flags an immediate structural evaluation error and terminates execution.

\subsection{Calculating number of credit units}
The final number of credit units ($\Delta U$) are scaled dynamically based on a string mapping logical condition checking account categories:
\begin{equation}
\Delta U = \frac{M_{net}}{\text{Tariff Rate}}
\end{equation}
Where:
\begin{equation}
\text{Tariff Rate} = 
\begin{cases} 250.0 \text{ UGX}, & \text{if Type } = \text{"Commercial"} \\ 
150.0 \text{ UGX}, & \text{if Type } = \text{"Domestic"} \end{cases}
\end{equation}

\section{Main requirements of the program.}
\begin{itemize}
    \item To receive household information and store it using structures.
    \item To be able to edit, update and delete the household information.
    \item To calculate the number of credit units depending on how much a user has input.
    \item The program should print a receite after the calculation of the credit units showing the units purchased and the balance of units.
    \item It should be able to print the summary of records of households stored in the system showing all their details including credit units and balance.
    \item The program should be able to detect leackage and low credit balance and display an appropriate error or warning message.
\end{itemize}

